Class EMXMessage

    public class EMXMessage
extends FIXMessageWithPluggableStore
    The parent class of all EMX message subclasses. This class contains much of the processing needed to manage EMX messages. Usually an EMXMessage will be an instance of a subclass of this class, but most of the message processing is done by this parent class.
    Author:
    Christopher J Burton, 25/Nov/2001.

    • Constructor Detail

      • EMXMessage

        public EMXMessage()
        Allow construction of an empty EMXMessage. The subclass that uses this constructor (it will probably be called by default) must fill the message details itself.

      • EMXMessage

        public EMXMessage(IFIXMessage message)
        Construct an EMXMessage from the given CameronFIX Message. It is the caller's responsibility to ensure that the given Message is a legal EMXMessage.

        Subclasses of EMXMessage implement this constructor so that an EMXMessage of the right subtype can be constructed.

        This constructor, and the corresponding constructors of all EMXMessage subclasses, is called by the reflection process that the static EMXMessage.castToType() method uses.

        Parameters:
        message - the message to construct from

      • EMXMessage

        public EMXMessage(String msgType,
                  String emxMsgID)
        Construct an untyped EMXMessage but nevertheless set the type fields with the indicated values. This is useful where a EMXMessage must be created but it does not have to be castToType. This is used in the EMXDelimitedFileAdapter. Creates An EMXMessage that HAS NOT been cast to the correct subclass. If a properly subclassed EMXMessage is required, then the program must call EMXMessage.castToType after calling this constructor.
        Parameters:
        msgType - the message type
        emxMsgID - the message ID

    • Method Detail

      • setDefaultSenderCompID

        public static void setDefaultSenderCompID(String senderCompID)
        Define a global default SenderCompID, which will be inserted into every new EMXMessage. The application may still provide a different SenderCompID to the constructor of particular messages, or change it before sending the message, even if this default value has been set.

        This is provided as an optional convenience facility, which will be useful to most simple applications. Applications that deal with more than one EMX connection using multiple SenderCompIDs should not set this global value.

        Parameters:
        senderCompID - the default global SenderCompID

      • setDefaultTargetCompID

        public static void setDefaultTargetCompID(String targetCompID)
        Define a global default TargetCompID, which will be inserted into every new EMXMessage. The application may still provide a different TargetCompID to the constructor of particular messages, or change it before sending the message, even if this default value has been set.

        However, since the EMX Hub always has a CompID of "EMX", it is unlikely that any application would want to set the TargetCompID to anything other than "EMX".

        Parameters:
        targetCompID - the default global TargetCompID

      • castToType

        public static IFIXMessage castToType(IFIXMessage message)
        Convert, if possible, a message to an appropriate subclass of EMXMessage. If the supplied message is not a type of EMXMessage, it is returned unchanged. If the message is changed, a new Message object of the right subclass of EMXMessage is returned and the new object's RoutingHint is made the same as the original message's RoutingHint.

        This method is used when an incoming message is received from the CameronFIX session. If it can be converted to an EMXMessage then it can be processed using the supporting methods of this class.

        Parameters:
        message - The message to be converted.
        Returns:
        The correctly subclassed message, if converted, or the original message that was supplied.

      • addEMXHeader

        protected final void addEMXHeader(String msgType,
                                  String emxMsgID)
        Add the standard EMXHeader fields to this message, including a field for DeliverToCompID. This method calls the addEMXHeader( String, String, boolean ) method with addDeliverToCompID set to true, which is the behaviour that is wanted when a participant is creating an EMXMessage.
        Parameters:
        msgType - the message type
        emxMsgID - the message ID

      • addEMXHeader

        protected final void addEMXHeader(String msgType,
                                  String emxMsgID,
                                  boolean addDeliverToCompID)
        Add the standard EMXHeader fields to this message. The DeliverToCompID is added only if addDeliverToCompID is set. The DeliverToCompID is not wanted when an EMX Hub (or Hub Emulator) is creating an EMXMessage, such as a MACK or a MERR. It is wanted, however, whenever a participant is creating an EMXMessage, and adding the DeliverToCompID field here ensures that it will be positioned in the message header section.
        Parameters:
        msgType - the message type
        emxMsgID - the message ID
        addDeliverToCompID - whether to add the DeliverToCompID

      • setReturnAddress

        protected final void setReturnAddress(EMXMessage request)
        Set the address of this message to reply to the supplied message. The address fields of this message are filled with the values required to ensure that the message will be delivered to the originator of the supplied request message.

        This method is intended to be used by those applications that respond to incoming messages, such as Fund Provider applications.

        Parameters:
        request - The received message to which this message is the reply.

      • copyField

        protected final void copyField(EMXMessage request,
                               int tag)
        Copy a field from a request message to this message.

        This method is intended to be used by those applications that respond to incoming messages, such as Fund Provider applications.

        Parameters:
        request - The received message to which this message is the reply.
        tag - The TAG code of the field to copy. It is not an error if the tag does not exist in the request message. In that case no action will be taken.

      • updateFrom

        public final void updateFrom(ITagValues fields)
        Updates this EMXMessage with the fields in the supplied ITagValues. Each ITagValue is read and setValue is called, so that any existing field with the supplied tag is updated, or a new field is added if not already present. So the supplied fields can be used to update a header field that may already be in the message. Note that if the user wants to add repeating fields to the message, so that the fields should all be added and not used to update any existing values, then he should use the appendFrom method instead.
        Parameters:
        fields - the fields to update from

      • getGroups

        public Iterator getGroups()

        Returns:
        An Iterator of MessageFields objects.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the message type does not have a repeating group structure.

      • addGroup

        public void addGroup(ITagValues element)
              throws Exception
        Add a repeating group element, provided in an ITagValues object, to the message. The first field must be the type defined by EMX to introduce the group element. Its value will be the element number and must be one more than the number currently in the field type defined by EMX to terminate the repeating group. This latter field must be present, since the new element will be inserted directly before it.
        Parameters:
        element - the element to add
        Throws:
        Exception - TBD

      • isHeaderField

        protected static boolean isHeaderField(int tag)
        A utility method to determine whether a given tag is a header field. This permits us, when creating a reply message in response to a request message, to find the point at which the request message's header ends and its application data begins.
        Parameters:
        tag - a tag
        Returns:
        whether the given tag is a header field

      • isTrailerField

        protected static boolean isTrailerField(int tag)
        A utility method to determine whether a given tag is a trailer field. This permits us, when creating a reply message in response to a request message, to find the point at which the request message's trailer begins. This may be the point at which we want to begin inserting new fields.
        Parameters:
        tag - a tag
        Returns:
        whether the given tag is a trailer field
